      "side": 1,
      "message": "Skia style leans a little more toward kBmpSize, but no one will be too confused reading BMP_SIZE.  They may just assume it\u0027s a macro.\n\nWe should probably mark these explicitly static.  It can be hard to remember that global const values are implicitly static, so an explicit static helps as a reminder.  Even if you know the rule, it can still be hard to know when it applies and when it doesn\u0027t (as a non-const pointer to const, TEST_FONT is _not_ implicitly static here, but the other 5 are).",
      "revId": "6dcbf21ac0ec67c246742e306b2e1a12989130a9",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
